------------------------------------------------------------------
KEY LESSON
------------------------------------------------------------------

When a PNG image challenge gives no obvious surface clues, open
StegSolve and cycle through every bit plane before using any
other tool. The LSB of the Blue channel (Blue 0) is the single
most common hiding spot in PNG steganography. Structured shapes
like QR codes, barcodes, or text in any bit plane immediately
confirm hidden data. Everything else in that plane will look
like random noise.
